namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.
namedLocations.name: Gujarat

namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.
namedLocations.name: ZIP Code

namedLocations.description: A caudex (plural: caudices) of a plant is a stem, but the term is also used to mean a rootstock and particularly a basal stem structure from which new growth arises. In the strict sense of the term, meaning a stem, "caudex" is most often used with plants that have a different stem morphology from the typical angiosperm dicotyledon stem: examples of this include palms, ferns, and cycads.
namedLocations.name: Caudex

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to our page shop.
In this video we will learn about how to design product templates.
Let's talk about key features and benefits.
With design template, you can offer various designs to your customers which can be created in the designer studio.
Templates section of the admin panel is broadly divided into two product templates and PDF block templates.
In the product template, we have customizable and non customizable templates.
Customizable templates.
These options will let customers to customize the template design.
From the design, they can change the text, images, background and more.
For example, business cards.
Non customizable templates.
These templates are the opposite of the customizable templates.
If you have a certain design which you don't want your customers to make changes into it, you can allocate those templates into a non customizable category.
Customers will get a direct option to check out after selecting such templates.
For example, yard signs.
Let's have a look into the admin.
So first of all, we need to go to the templates.
Click on product templates and here you can see all your templates created and to add a new template you have to click on add button at the top right corner.
So once you click over there here you need to fill these details.
So you have to first select user type.
So in this you have all store, default store or private store.
So if you want to create a template for all the stores, you can select all store.

If you want to set this template for your retail customers or retail store you can select default store or if you want to set a template for your private stores you can select all store or any specific private store from the list.
Here we are taking default store and then you have to select product type.
So in the product type you have to select standard.
If you have additional or like add on service you can select those.
So here we are taking standard product type and then we have to select the product in which we need to assign the template.
So here we are taking one product.
So with the size 2 by 3.5 business card we have selected now we have to select template category.
So here we can set this as one category name, business, services or we can take another category for example marketing or advertisement.
So here we have selected template categories.
Now we can set colour for template filter.
So if you want to set any colour filter for this particular template, you can choose from the list or you can add a new colour category.
If you want to create new you can just click on add button and you can create your own colour category or you can add your own colour option over here.
Now we we need to put the title so, so here we are putting title.
So here we can see the duplicate product.
In this we have those products in which the size is similar to the product we have selected for this template.
So if the bleed size is similar you will see duplicate products into this section.
So you can copy the template into those via this section.
So you can choose the products and assign to the assigned product section.
Next we have group name.
So you can add a group name if you want to show this template into a group.
And next we have template type.
So you need to choose template type.
So here we have customizable non customizable PDF block uploaded print ready EF and template layout.
Here we are creating customizable template.
So we will choose customizable only and the next we have template cost.
So you can also put template cost for your template design.
So for this there is a setting into the back end.
So if you go to the store configuration site settings you have to search cost and here you can see enable template cost.
So you can enable this select yes and your template cost section will be enabled in your templates.
So you can put any price if you want to show additional cost for this template.
Next, we have template personalization.
So this button is basically we use for the autofilled template like PDF blocks.
So we don't need to enable this at the moment.
And next we need to make the status active.
And also you can set the sorting order over here.
Now just click on save and continue.
So here you can see the designer studio is showing up where we can see your design.
So you can create any design like you can put a clip art and make any design which you want.
You can choose the color as well like here.
And then similarly for the backside, you can put the text logo and design on your template.
After creating your design, you have to click on save and you can click on continue to complete this design.
So now when you go to the front in this product, let's take a look into the storefront.
So this is our created design where customer can put the details like company name, name, title, e-mail, website and they can continue check out with the with this design.
This is how the templates they can proceed further with the checkout.
Let's talk about the non customizable templates.
So in this similarly, we have to add the template details like user type and you have to select product type standard and we have to choose the product into which we need to assign the template.
And we can put the title and category we can select let's say animals and pets.
And if you want to duplicate the template, you can choose duplicate product.
And after that you we have to select on customizable template.
And if you want to put the template cost, you can put and set the sorting order and make the status active.
Now just click on save and continue.
So here you can create a new design in the blank canvas.
So let's say this design we have created.
So this is a sign we created for a warning like dog inside.
Now click on save and continue.
So as you can see here our design is created and now when we go to the storefront now we go to the product and click on templates.
And here we can see there is a non customizable template.
So customer can only see this template, they cannot do any changes into it and just click on checkout.
In this way the non customizable template works.
Thank you for watching this video.
In case of any further concern, feel free to connect with us.
